\f0\fs24 \cf0 # CODING STANDARDS & RULES FOR "THE JAR"\
\
## 1. Tech Stack\
- Framework: Next.js 14+ (App Router)\
- Language: TypeScript\
- Styling: Tailwind CSS\
- Components: Shadcn UI (Radix Primitives)\
- Icons: Lucide React\
- Database: Supabase (Use @supabase/ssr)\
- State: React Query (Tanstack Query) for client-side data, Server Actions for mutations.\
\
## 2. Component Architecture\
- Use **React Server Components (RSC)** by default.\
- Only use `"use client"` when interactivity (hooks, event listeners) is required.\
- Place all data fetching in Server Components or Server Actions.\
- Use `zod` for form validation.\
\
## 3. Styling Guidelines (The "Geological Industrial" Look)\
- **Backgrounds:** Use `bg-slate-50` for app canvas, `bg-white` for cards.\
- **Borders:** Heavy use of borders. Use `border-slate-200` for containers.\
- **Typography:** Use `font-mono` (Geist/JetBrains) for headers, IDs, and financial data. Use `font-sans` (Inter) for body text.\
- **Key Colors:**\
  - Rocks: `bg-slate-800` text-white\
  - Water/Shield: `bg-blue-600`\
  - Sand: `bg-stone-200` text-stone-900\
  - Beacon: `text-amber-500` or `bg-amber-500`\
\
## 4. Folder Structure\
- `/app`: All routes.\
- `/components/ui`: Shadcn primitives.\
- `/components/features`: Feature-specific components (e.g., `CommitmentBoard`, `SensorLog`).\
- `/lib/supabase`: Supabase clients (server/client).\
- `/actions`: Server Actions for mutations (e.g., `createEngagement`, `lightBeacon`).}